AU  - Mann, William
T1  - The Incidence of Student Loan Subsidies: Evidence from the PLUS Program
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhac031
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 36
IS  - 4
SP  - 1621
EP  - 1666
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - How much do students benefit from student loan subsidies? We investigate this question, exploiting a natural experiment: a demand shock due to the 2011 tightening of credit standards in the PLUS program. We first establish that the Bennett hypothesis is best explained by colleges charging large markups over their marginal costs, rather than by advantageous selection. Then we use our results to estimate that students plausibly capture less than 60 cents of each dollar of resources expended on loan subsidies. We discuss alternative approaches that would more directly benefit students.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhac031
ER  - 



